rComments: She is really nice and makes the material really clear in lectures.
One of the most coherent profs I've ever had.

Bahar's a pretty great prof, and she does a lot of examples in class, so you have a clear idea of how to approach problems. Assignments were fair, and the problems were actually kinda fun. My only gripe would be lectures felt slow sometimes, but that's because some people were asking too many questions in my section.

Bahar gives lots of examples in class. This is good because it gives a clear proof outline, and helps for assignments and the midterm/exam as redoing the examples gives you a chance to practice. (Practice is really important in this course!) Bahar explains really well and is so kind, too! Would definitely take again.
She puts in a lot of effort and is a really good prof even though she is in research stream. She is a better prof than a lot of profs in teaching stream.
My favorite prof in second year cs, she really puts in the effort

Bahar goes above and beyond in providing help for her students. The course notes (the textbook) is quite daunting and hard to follow, which is why her lectures are very important. Her notes, solutions, and posts on Piazza are clear and very easy to follow. The course was structured in a way where you get constant feedback and lots of practice.

Bahar is one of the most helpful people I've ever met. The material is tough but she goes above and beyond to make sure you're on the right track. She's also a good lecturer; doesn't go too fast and takes time to explain things.

Bahar is a good professor, however because she is teaching such large classes you need to go to her office hours to get the most from her teaching. She is very helpful if you can talk to her in person, and will walk you through any topics that you don't find clear which is imperative in a class like csc236.

One of the few teachers willing to actually sit down and work through a problem with a student, should they approach her and ask. Also one of the few math or CS teachers to actually use a digital drawing tablet over a traditional chalkboard. Which is just great, b/c you never have to worry about missing a step!

Her teaching ability in class is terrible, however if you approached her during her office hours, she can teach exceptionally well (which is quite weird). I would say that she needs to work on her ability to teach in front of a big crowd.  The material in CSC165 is quite challenging, so as soon as you do not understand something, seek help!

Granted, her lectures were a bit of a struggle, but she makes up for it in her office hours. So many of my questions were cleared up in her office hours, and I ended up well in the course. All in all, CSC165 is no cakewalk but Bahar is definitely there for you.

When i took this course it was shared between two instructors. Although Bahar was the clearer of the two, both presented material in a very confusing manner. I feel that my mark suffered because of this.   Help was, however, always available.

I don't usually write these. But Professor Bahar has been one of the best professors I have. If you are not shy and put in the effort, she will put in the effort to care about her students. What she lacks with "her accent", she makes up for with clear and concise notes. Her responses on Piazza are always helpful. I have an academic crush.
